cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the subgroups of Twitter and Facebook users who consume and distribute junk news related to military affairs and national security issues.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of social media disinformation campaigns on military personnel and veterans.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper touches upon national security issues and the spread of misinformation on social media.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the technical aspects of how junk news is disseminated on social media platforms.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may analyze the use of multimedia content in junk news related to military affairs and national security issues.
